{"title_page": "1971\u201372 West Midlands (Regional) League", "text_new": "The '''1971\u201372 West Midlands (Regional) League season''' was the 72nd in the history of the [[West Midlands (Regional) League]], an English [[association football]] competition for semi-professional and amateur teams based in the [[West Midlands (county)|West Midlands county]], [[Shropshire]], [[Herefordshire]], [[Worcestershire]] and southern [[Staffordshire]].\n\n==Premier Division==\n{{Infobox football league season\n|competition = West Midlands League<br>Premier Division\n|season=1971\u201372\n|winners=[[Tamworth F.C.|Tamworth]]\n|promoted=six clubs\n|relegated=\n|matches=342\n|total goals=1052\n|prevseason= [[1970\u201371 West Midlands (Regional) League#Premier Division|1970\u201371]]\n|nextseason= [[1972\u201373 West Midlands (Regional) League#Premier Division|1972\u201373]]\n}}\n\nThe Premier Division featured 17 clubs which competed in the division last season, along with two new clubs:\n*GKN Sankeys, promoted from Division One\n*[[Warley F.C.|Warley]], transferred from the [[1970\u201371 Midland Football League|Midland Football League]]\n\nAlso, Redditch changed name to [[Redditch United F.C.|Redditch United]].\n\n===League table===\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style=WDL\n|section=Premier Division\n|use_goal_ratio=y\n|winpoints=2\n|res_col_header=PR\n\n|team1=TAM|name_TAM=[[Tamworth F.C.|Tamworth]]\n|team2=ATH|name_ATH=[[Atherstone Town F.C.|Atherstone Town]]\n|team3=KID|name_KID=[[Kidderminster Harriers F.C.|Kidderminster Harriers]]\n|team4=BRO|name_BRO=[[Bromsgrove Rovers F.C.|Bromsgrove Rovers]]\n|team5=BIL|name_BIL=[[Bilston Town F.C.|Bilston]]\n|team6=RED|name_RED=[[Redditch United F.C.|Redditch United]]\n|team7=LYE|name_LYE=[[Lye Town F.C.|Lye Town]]\n|team8=HED|name_HED=[[Hednesford Town F.C.|Hednesford]]\n|team9=DUD|name_DUD=[[Dudley Town F.C.|Dudley Town]]\n|team10=BED|name_BED=[[Bedworth United F.C.|Bedworth United]]\n|team11=EAS|name_EAS=[[Eastwood Hanley F.C.|Eastwood Hanley]]\n|team12=GOR|name_GOR=[[Gornal Athletic F.C.|Lower Gornal Athletic]]\n|team13=GKN|name_GKN=GKN Sankeys\n|team14=WAR|name_WAR=[[Warley F.C.|Warley]]\n|team15=BHA|name_BHA=[[Brierley Hill Alliance F.C.|Brierley Hill Alliance]]\n|team16=WOL|name_WOL=[[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] \"A\"\n|team17=DAR|name_DAR=[[Darlaston F.C.|Darlaston]]\n|team18=HAL|name_HAL=[[Halesowen Town F.C.|Halesowen Town]]\n|team19=HIN|name_HIN=[[Hinckley Athletic F.C.|Hinckley Athletic]]\n\n|win_ATH=24|draw_ATH=7|loss_ATH=5|gf_ATH=74|ga_ATH=32\n|win_BED=14|draw_BED=8|loss_BED=14|gf_BED=72|ga_BED=64\n|win_BIL=16|draw_BIL=9|loss_BIL=11|gf_BIL=63|ga_BIL=37\n|win_BHA=11|draw_BHA=6|loss_BHA=19|gf_BHA=47|ga_BHA=58\n|win_BRO=22|draw_BRO=8|loss_BRO=6|gf_BRO=74|ga_BRO=39\n|win_DAR=6|draw_DAR=11|loss_DAR=19|gf_DAR=34|ga_DAR=68\n|win_DUD=13|draw_DUD=12|loss_DUD=11|gf_DUD=37|ga_DUD=36\n|win_EAS=13|draw_EAS=9|loss_EAS=14|gf_EAS=51|ga_EAS=58\n|win_GKN=10|draw_GKN=10|loss_GKN=16|gf_GKN=38|ga_GKN=63\n|win_GOR=13|draw_GOR=6|loss_GOR=17|gf_GOR=47|ga_GOR=60\n|win_HAL=3|draw_HAL=12|loss_HAL=21|gf_HAL=41|ga_HAL=77\n|win_HED=16|draw_HED=6|loss_HED=14|gf_HED=65|ga_HED=59\n|win_HIN=4|draw_HIN=8|loss_HIN=24|gf_HIN=26|ga_HIN=83\n|win_KID=23|draw_KID=7|loss_KID=6|gf_KID=84|ga_KID=32\n|win_LYE=14|draw_LYE=10|loss_LYE=12|gf_LYE=52|ga_LYE=46\n|win_RED=17|draw_RED=6|loss_RED=13|gf_RED=75|ga_RED=59\n|win_TAM=25|draw_TAM=7|loss_TAM=4|gf_TAM=81|ga_TAM=38\n|win_WAR=13|draw_WAR=3|loss_WAR=20|gf_WAR=56|ga_WAR=75\n|win_WOL=7|draw_WOL=11|loss_WOL=18|gf_WOL=35|ga_WOL=68\n|col_P=#D0F0C0|text_P=Promoted to the [[1972\u201373 Southern Football League#Division One North|Southern Football League]]\n|result1=P|result2=P|result3=P|result4=P|result6=P|result10=P\n|col_T=#CCCCFF|text_T=Transferred to the [[1972\u201373 Midland Football League|Midland Football League]]\n|result8=T\n|class_rules=1) points; 2) goal ratio.\n|update=complete\n|source=[https://www.nonleaguematters.co.uk/nlmnet/Addon