ws |title=Quezon province confirms first COVID-19 patient |url=https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/3/15/quezon-province-first-case-coronavirus.html |accessdate=March 30, 2020 |work=CNN Philippines |date=March 15, 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Quezon]]<ref name=\"surges\"/>\n**[[Rizal]]<ref name=\"CNNPH-CovidRizal\">{{cite news |title=Rizal governor tests positive for COVID-19 |url=https://www.cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/3/25/Nini-Ynares-COVID-19-coronavirus.html |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=CNN Philippines |date=March 25, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n*[[Mimaropa]]<!---Region IV-B designation has been dropped, since 2016; despite Calabarzon still being designated as Region IV-A--->\n**[[Marinduque]]<ref name=\"Inquirer-CovidMarinduque\">{{cite news |last1=Cinco |first1=Maricar |title=Torrijos town resident is Marinduque\u2019s first COVID-19 case |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1247100/torrijos-town-resident-is-marinduques-first-covid-19-case |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Philippine Daily Inquirer |date=March 23, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n**[[Occidental Mindoro]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=Virola |first1=Madonna |title=Deceased man is 1st COVID-19 case of Occidental Mindoro |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1249506/deceased-woman-is-1st-covid-19-case-of-occidental-mindoro |accessdate=March 30, 2020 |work=Philippine Daily Inquirer |date=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Oriental Mindoro]]<ref name=\"surges\"/>\n<!---No cases yet in Palawan outside Puerto Princessa--->\n**''[[Puerto Princesa]]''<ref name=\"Inquirer-CovidPalawan\">{{cite news |last1=Miranda |first1=Romar |title=Palawan records first COVID-19 case |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1246013/palawan-records-first-covid-19-case |accessdate=March 31, 2020 |work=Philippine Daily Inquirer |date=March 21, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n*[[Bicol Region]] (Region V)\n**[[Albay]]<ref name=bicolfirst>{{cite news |title=Bicol region records first cases of COVID-19 |url=https://www.cnnphilippines.com/regional/2020/3/27/bicol-coron