{"title_page": "The Brain Leeches", "text_new": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Brain Leeches\n| image          = \n| alt            = \n| director       = [[Fred Olen Ray]]\n| producer       = Fred Olen Ray\n| writer         = Jim Kennedy<br>[[Brad Linaweaver]]<br>Fred Olen Ray\n| based on       = \n| starring       = Paul Jones<br>Marcia Scott<br>Ray Starr\n| music          = Paul Jones<br>Sugar Lee<br>[[Modest Mussorgsky]]\n| cinematography = Marvin Levine<br>John Raber<br>Fred Olen Ray<br><small>(as Fred Ray)</small>\n| editing        = \n| studio         = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|1978}}\n| runtime        = 55 minutes\n| country        = \n| language       = English\n| budget         = $298.00\n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''The Brain Leeches''''' is an [[low-budget film|ultra low-budget]] 1978 [[science fiction film|sci-fi]] [[exploitation film]] directed by [[Fred Olen Ray]] and starring Paul Jones, Marcia Scott & Ray Starr.\n\n==Production==\nPolitical essayist [[Brad Linaweaver]] received his first original story credit (for film) for ''The Brain Leeches''. The experience changed the trajectory of Linaweaver's career path, emphasizing film and science fiction writing for the rest of his life.<ref name=\"Investigator\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodinvestigator.com/2007/linaweaver.htm|title=Libertarian Screenwriter Brad Linaweaver Slams Neocons|publisher=Hollywood Investigator|date=August 12, 2007|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Memorium\">{{citeweb|url= https://amazingstories.com/2019/09/in-memoriam-brad-linaweaver/|title=In Memoriam-Brad Linaweaver|publisher=AmazingStories.com|date=September 12, 2019|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>  The film also jump started the career of prodigious Hollywood director/producer (and sometimes professional wrestler<ref name=\"Boggs2014\">{{cite book|author=Johnny D. Boggs|title=Jesse James and the Movies|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-TLXYhM3cTkC&pg=PA225|date=10 January 2014|publisher=McFarland|isbn=978-0-7864-8496-6|page=225}}</ref>) Fred Olen Ray, who subsequently lent [[Quentin Tarantino]] his first 16mm camera when he was making ''[[My Best Friend's Birthday]]''.<ref name=\"Locus\">{{cite web|url=https://locusmag.com/2019/09/brad-linaweaver-1952-2019/|title=Brad Linaweaver (1952-2019)|publisher=Locus Publications|date=September 3, 2019|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2007/film/news/q-a-with-tarantino-when-he-was-mr-green-1117961178/|title=Q&A with Tarantino\u2026when he was Mr. Green|first=Steve|last=Gaydos|website=Variety|date=14 March 2007|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref> The association and collaboration between Linaweaver and Ray continued until Linaweaver's death in 2019.<ref name=\"Locus\" />\n\nThe film was shot using an old [[Auricon|Auricon 16mm camera]], and (expired) nine-year-old [[black and white]] film stock obtained from Ray's employer, an [[Orlando, Florida]] television station.<ref name=\"Ray1991\">{{cite book|author=Fred Olen Ray|title=The New Poverty Row: Independent Filmmakers as Distributors|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=H9GknfDYd4sC&pg=PA176|date=1 January 1991|publisher=McFarland|isbn=978-0-89950-628-9|page=176}}</ref><ref name=\"Quarles2010\">{{cite book|author=Mike Quarles|title=Down and Dirty: Hollywood's Exploitation Filmmakers and Their Movies|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=L5iRMlzjbSEC&pg=PA80|date=21 June 2010|publisher=McFarland|isbn=978-0-7864-6257-5|page=80}}</ref> The alien invaders were represented by large rubber ants, purchased at a [[dime store]] for 19 cents each.<ref name=\"Ray1991\" /> Earthlings under mind control by the aliens were portrayed as having all-white eyes. The [[special effect]] was achieved by applying white tape to the actors' eyelids.<ref name=\"Ray1991\" /> The destruction of the alien headquarters (the TV station where Ray worked) was depicted using stock footage of a nuclear explosion, from an old 16mm documentary found in the television station film archive.<ref name=\"Ray1991\" /> The film score is a [[public domain]] recording of [[Moussorgsky]]'s [[Pictures at an Exhibition]], taken directly from a \"cheap record album\". According to Ray: \"No effort was made to synchronize any of the music to the picture\".<ref name=\"Ray1991\" /> Portions of the film were shot at a bar (The Foxhead Tavern) in Orlando.<ref>{{cite newspaper|url=https://orlandosentinel.newspapers.com/clip/16774450/the-brain-leeches/|title=\"The Brain Leeches\"|publisher=[[The Orlando Sentinel]]|page=133|date=May 28, 1978|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref> \n\nProduction of ''The Brain Leeches'' was completed, on budget, for $298.00.<ref name=\"Ray1991\" /><ref name=\"Quarles2010\"/>\n\n==Plot==\nA former nuclear scientist turned pro-wrestler does battle with invading aliens who are taking over the brains of folks in a small town.<ref name=\"Ray1991\" />\n\n==Distribution==\nIn 1991, Ray stated that ''The Brain Leeches'' had been shown publicly only one time, and that it would never be released for distribution.<ref name=\"Ray1991\" /> However, in recent years, copies have become available through distributors such as Sinister Cinema.com.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.sinistercinema.com/product.asp?specific=33963|title=Sci Fi BRAIN LEECHES, THE*|publisher=Sinister Cinema.com|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>  \n\n==Cast==\n*Paul Jones as Dr. John Hayes\n*Marcia Scott as Susan\n*Ray Starr as Rusty Fender\n*Jennifer Knight as Rose\n*[[Brad Linaweaver]] as Billy Johnson\n*[[Fred Olen Ray]] (as Brian Wolfe) as Tom\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*''[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0075780/?ref_=fn_al_tt_1 The Brain Leeches]'' at [[Internet Movie Database]]\n*''[http://movies.msn.com/movies/movie/the-brain-leeches/ The Brain Leeches]'' at Movies.msn.com\n\n{{Fred Olen Ray}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Brain Leeches}}\n[[Category:1970s science fiction horror films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Fred Olen Ray]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American science fiction horror films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Brain Leeches\n| image          = \n| alt            = \n| director       = [[Fred Olen Ray]]\n| producer       = Fred Olen Ray\n| writer         = Jim Kennedy<br>[[Brad Linaweaver]]<br>Fred Olen Ray\n| based on       = \n| starring       = Paul Jones<br>Marcia Scott<br>Ray Starr\n| music          = Paul Jones<br>Sugar Lee<br>[[Modest Mussorgsky]]\n| cinematography = Marvin Levine<br>John Raber<br>Fred Olen Ray<br><small>(as Fred Ray)</small>\n| editing        = \n| studio         = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|1978}}\n| runtime        = 55 minutes\n| country        = \n| language       = English\n| budget         = $298.00\n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''The Brain Leeches''''' is an [[low-budget film|ultra low-budget]] 1978 [[science fiction film|sci-fi]] [[exploitation film]] directed by [[Fred Olen Ray]] and starring Paul Jones, Marcia Scott & Ray Starr.\n\n==Production==\nPolitical essayist [[Brad Linaweaver]] received his first original story credit (for film) for ''The Brain Leeches''. The experience changed the trajectory of Linaweaver's career path, emphasizing film and science fiction writing for the rest of his life.<ref name=\"Investigator\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodinvestigator.com/2007/linaweaver.htm|title=Libertarian Screenwriter Brad Linaweaver Slams Neocons|publisher=Hollywood Investigator|date=August 12, 2007|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Memorium\">{{citeweb|url= https://amazingstories.com/2019/09/in-memoriam-brad-linaweaver/|title=In Memoriam-Brad Linaweaver|publisher=AmazingStories.com|date=September 12, 2019|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>  The film also jump started the career of prodigious Hollywood director/producer (and sometimes professional wrestler<ref name=\"Boggs2014\">{{cite book|author=Johnny D. Boggs|title=Jesse James and the Movies|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-TLXYhM3cTkC&pg=PA225|date=10 January 2014|publisher=McFarland|isbn=978-0-7864-8496-6|page=225}}</ref>) Fred Olen Ray, who later went on to lend [[Quentin Tarantino]] his first 16mm camera when he was making ''[[My Best Friend's Birthday]]''.<ref name=\"Locus\">{{cite web|url=https://locusmag.com/2019/09/brad-linaweaver-1952-2019/|title=Brad Linaweaver (1952-2019)|publisher=Locus Publications|date=September 3, 2019|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2007/film/news/q-a-with-tarantino-when-he-was-mr-green-1117961178/|title=Q&A with Tarantino\u2026when he was Mr. Green|first=Steve|last=Gaydos|website=Variety|date=14 March 2007|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref> The association and collaboration between Linaweaver and Ray continued until Linaweaver's death in 2019.<ref name=\"Locus\" />\n\nThe film was shot using an old [[Auricon|Auricon 16mm camera]], and (expired) nine-year-old [[black and white]] film stock obtained from Ray's employer, an [[Orlando, Florida]] television station.<ref name=\"Ray1991\">{{cite book|author=Fred Olen Ray|title=The New Poverty Row: Independent Filmmakers as Distributors|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=H9GknfDYd4sC&pg=PA176|date=1 January 1991|publisher=McFarland|isbn=978-0-89950-628-9|page=176}}</ref><ref name=\"Quarles2010\">{{cite book|author=Mike Quarles|title=Down and Dirty: Hollywood's Exploitation Filmmakers and Their Movies|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=L5iRMlzjbSEC&pg=PA80|date=21 June 2010|publisher=McFarland|isbn=978-0-7864-6257-5|page=80}}</ref> The alien invaders were represented by large rubber ants, purchased at a [[dime store]] for 19 cents each.<ref name=\"Ray1991\" /> Earthlings under mind control by the aliens were portrayed as having all-white eyes. The [[special effect]] was achieved by applying white tape to the actors' eyelids.<ref name=\"Ray1991\" /> The destruction of the alien headquarters (the TV station where Ray worked) was depicted using stock footage of a nuclear explosion, from an old 16mm documentary found in the television station film archive.<ref name=\"Ray1991\" /> The film score is a [[public domain]] recording of [[Moussorgsky]]'s [[Pictures at an Exhibition]], taken directly from a \"cheap record album\". According to Ray: \"No effort was made to synchronize any of the music to the picture\".<ref name=\"Ray1991\" /> Portions of the film were shot at a bar (The Foxhead Tavern) in Orlando.<ref>{{cite newspaper|url=https://orlandosentinel.newspapers.com/clip/16774450/the-brain-leeches/|title=\"The Brain Leeches\"|publisher=[[The Orlando Sentinel]]|page=133|date=May 28, 1978|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref> \n\nProduction of ''The Brain Leeches'' was completed, on budget, for $298.00.<ref name=\"Ray1991\" /><ref name=\"Quarles2010\"/>\n\n==Plot==\nA former nuclear scientist turned pro-wrestler does battle with invading aliens who are taking over the brains of folks in a small town.<ref name=\"Ray1991\" />\n\n==Distribution==\nIn 1991, Ray stated that ''The Brain Leeches'' had been shown publicly only one time, and that it would never be released for distribution.<ref name=\"Ray1991\" /> However, in recent years, copies have become available through distributors such as Sinister Cinema.com.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.sinistercinema.com/product.asp?specific=33963|title=Sci Fi BRAIN LEECHES, THE*|publisher=Sinister Cinema.com|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>  \n\n==Cast==\n*Paul Jones as Dr. John Hayes\n*Marcia Scott as Susan\n*Ray Starr as Rusty Fender\n*Jennifer Knight as Rose\n*[[Brad Linaweaver]] as Billy Johnson\n*[[Fred Olen Ray]] (as Brian Wolfe) as Tom\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*''[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0075780/?ref_=fn_al_tt_1 The Brain Leeches]'' at [[Internet Movie Database]]\n*''[http://movies.msn.com/movies/movie/the-brain-leeches/ The Brain Leeches]'' at Movies.msn.com\n\n{{Fred Olen Ray}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Brain Leeches}}\n[[Category:1970s science fiction horror films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Fred Olen Ray]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American science fiction horror films]]\n", "name_user": "Gulbenk", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eProduction", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Brain_Leeches"}
{"title_page": "Korean Friendship Association", "text_new": "{{short description|Voluntary association}}\n{{third-party|date=May 2016}}\n{{Infobox organization\n|name           = Korean Friendship Association\n|image          = Korean Friendship Association.png\n|image_border   = \n|size           = \n|alt            = \n|caption        = Korean Friendship Association logo\n|map            = \n|msize          = \n|malt           = \n|mcaption       = \n|abbreviation   = KFA\n|motto          = \n|formation      = {{Start date|2000|11}}\n|extinction     = \n|type           = \n|status         = \n|purpose        = Official government cultural liaison agency for [[North Korea]] \n|headquarters   = \n|location       = Spain\n|region_served  = World\n|membership     = \n|language       = English\n|leader_title   = President\n|leader_name    = [[Alejandro Cao de Ben\u00f3s de Les y P\u00e9rez]]\n|main_organ     = \n|parent_organization = \n|affiliations   = \n|num_staff      = \n|num_volunteers = \n|budget         = \n|website        = {{URL|http://www.korea-dpr.com/kfa.html}}\n|remarks        = Hymn: [[Song of National Defense]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/NorthKoreaDPRK/status/326299450966421504|title=Official KFA Hymn Song of National Defence|publisher=KFA Official Twitter Account|date=April 22, 2013|accessdate=December 12, 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n\nThe '''Korean Friendship Association''' ({{lang-es|Asociaci\u00f3n de Amistad con Corea}}) is a [[Spain|Spanish]]-based friendship association with [[North Korea]]. The KFA was established in November 2000.<ref name=\"James2012\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nknews.org/2012/01/useful-idiots-the-curious-case-of-britains-pro-north-korean-community/|title='Useful Idiots'? The curious case of Britain's pro-North Korean Community|first=\nAlexander|last=James|date=29 January 2012|access-date=27 May 2016|website=NK News}}</ref> It has official representatives in 34 countries, including [[Argentina]], [[Belgium]], [[Brazil]], [[Canada]], [[China]], the [[Czech Republic]], [[Germany]], [[Greece]], [[Israel]] and [[State of Palestine|Palestine]], [[Italy]], [[Mexico]], [[Morocco]], [[Norway]], [[Peru]], [[Russia]], Spain, [[Switzerland]], [[Turkey]], the [[United Kingdom]], and the [[United States]].{{Citation needed lead|date=December 2016}}\n\nIts president, [[Spain|Spanish]] citizen [[Alejandro Cao de Ben\u00f3s de Les y P\u00e9rez]], is the only person paid a salary. Fees collected by the KFA are generally deposited in accounts in his name around Europe.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Capitalist credentials: N. Korea sympathizer group's huge profit on access to country|url = http://www.nknews.org/2015/01/capitalist-credentials-n-korea-sympathizer-groups-huge-profit-on-access-to-country/|website = NK News - North Korea News|access-date = 2016-01-13}}</ref>\n\n==Line==\nCompared with other North Korea friendship associations, the KFA is more radical.<ref name=\"Diplomat2014\">{{cite web|url=http://thediplomat.com/2014/02/the-westerners-who-love-north-korea/|title=The Westerners Who Love North Korea|first=Johan|last=Nylander|date=25 February 2014|access-date=27 May 2016|work=The Diplomat}}</ref>\n\nThe KFA pages provides North Korean related material, including tourism tips and political essays, and it is possible to hear views from a North Korean perspective. The KFA Forum site is hosted and administered in Europe and gives links to Korean language teaching sites.\n\nThe KFA denies violations of [[human rights in North Korea]] and disputes the existence of [[List of concentration and internment camps#North Korea|North Korean concentration camps]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Alejandro Cao de Ben\u00f3s Interview Part 2|work=One Free Korea|author=Enzo Reale|date=February 7, 2010|url= http://freekorea.us/2010/02/07/alejandro-cao-de-benos-interview-%E2%80%93-part-2/|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref>  \n\nThe objectives of the KFA are to promote the well-being of all members and to promote friendship between members of the KFA worldwide.\n\n===Objectives===\nThe stated objectives of the KFA are:<ref>http://www.korea-dpr.com/kfa.html</ref>\n* get up smoke a joint. \n* eat a big mac meal . \n* go home and have a powerwank.\n\nThe KFA organizes travel delegations to North Korea.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1699876,00.html|title=Postcard. North Korea|first=Jeann|last=\nGearey|date=3 January 2008|access-date=27 May 2016|website=Time|url-access=subscription }}</ref> Travel is according to experts a primary motivation of membership in KFA: partakers in trips are offered privileged service.<ref name=\"Harlan2012\"/>\n\n==Structure==\nThe KFA is the largest friendship association with North Korea.<ref name=\"Diplomat2014\"/> It operates in 120 countries. There is an Official Delegate in 34 countries. The KFA is licensed by the [[North Korean government]] and is well-funded and supported. The organization is coordinated well \"to a certain degree\", according to [[NK News]].<ref name=\"James2012\"/>\n\nThe national associations under the KFA do not receive official funding and operate \"as far less than consulates, just slightly more than fan clubs\".<ref name=\"Harlan2012\"/> They do not have many functions to support the government of North Korea: they do not support the regime monetarily and do not gather intelligence.<ref name=\"Harlan2012\">{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/asia_pacific/n-korea-finds-a-purpose-for-small-group-of-friends/2012/02/24/gIQAGHuImR_story.html|title=\nN. Korea finds a purpose for small group of 'friends'|first=Chico|last=Harlan|date=March 2, 2012|access-date=27 May 2016|website=The Washington Post}}</ref>\n\nOfficial Delegates are responsible for the activities in his/her country and secretaries appointed by the delegates. Above the Official Delegates, the \"International Organization Committee\" consisting of the President, the International Counselor and an International Organization Secretary who control and direct the activities of the KFA worldwide.\n*President: Alejandro Cao de Ben\u00f3s de Les y P\u00e9rez\n*International organization secretary: Mana Sapmak\n*International communication secretary: Carlos Luna\n*International Self-Elected Secretariat: Cory Ray Pope Giles-d'Leeuw\n*International commissar: Trever Aritz <ref>[http://korea-dpr.com/organization.html Official homepage]</ref>\n*Some of the most active members are Dr. Dermot Hudson, the Official Delegate in the United Kingdom who has been a part of KFA since its beginning and Trevor Spencer, the Official Delegate in Canada who is an active political writer and commentator.\n*Only one person has 4 countries as Zone delegate, Mr. Ulrich Larsen from Denmark. Ulrich Larsen is the Zone delegate in Scandinavia, meaning that he is in charge of Denmark, Finland, Norway, and Sweden. Larsen is known for making films about North Korea to YouTube for propaganda use. Both Dr. Dermot Hudson and Ulrich Larsen have been awarded medals by the North Korean government. \n\n==Criticism==\n[[NK News]] describes the KFA as \"one of the DPRK's primary tools of soft power within its global propaganda network\".<ref name=\"James2012\"/>\n\nJournalist David Scofield of [[Asia Times|Asia Times Online]] called members of KFA \"[[useful idiot]]s\",<ref name=\"Scofield2005\"/> described the organization as follows:\n\n<blockquote>The group's activities include \"information\" seminars where the enlightened benevolence of Kim's rule is championed, all part of its \"alternative\" view of the North. The ragged wretched displays of poverty and starvation are edited out and the voice of North Koreans not in the direct employ of Kim Jong-il are conspicuously absent. In place of uncomfortable reality, the KFA offers vacation photos of \"their\" North Korea taken during recent, state-supported visits, complete with bowling, golf, amusement parks and Karaoke with young female party members. Members write glowing pieces, oblations celebrating Kim Jong-il's wise rule. No starving people, torture, summary execution, penury or despair in the Korean Friendship Association's North Korea. Just golf, great meals and evenings in the company of Kim Jong-il's beauties.<ref name=\"Scofield2005\">{{cite web|url=http://www.atimes.com/atimes/Korea/GB03Dg02.html|title=\t\nKim Jong-il's 'useful idiots' in the West|first=David|last=Scofield|date=February 3, 2005|accessdate=December 28, 2013}}</ref></blockquote>\n\nA 2015 investigation by NK News found the commercial practices and integrity of the KFA to be in question.<ref>[http://www.nknews.org/2015/01/capitalist-credentials-n-korea-sympathizer-groups-huge-profit-on-access-to-country/ Capitalist credentials: N. Korea sympathizer group's huge profit on access to country]</ref>\n\nAccording to Hazel Smith of [[Cranfield University]], KFA associations have lost much of their original role as part of an international socialist movement. Today, they are reduced to serving domestic purposes of North Korea.<ref name=\"Harlan2012\"/>\n\n===International relations===\n\nThe KFA does not recognize, support or refer to any other Korean Friendship Associations around the world, including those who provide humanitarian aid as a main part of their action plan.  They refuse to create links on their own website to these organisations seeing themselves as \"the one and only Korean Friendship Association\", however, they are willing to participate in seminars and meetings in Pyongyang with these other international organisations.{{Citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|North Korea}}\n\n* [[Politics of North Korea]]\n* [[Propaganda in North Korea]]\n* [[Cultural diplomacy]]\n* [[Public diplomacy]]\n* [[Swedish-Korean Association]]\n* [[British Council]]\n* [[Alliance Fran\u00e7aise]]\n* [[German-American Bund]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website}}\n\n[[Category:Spanish friendship associations]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 2000]]\n[[Category:2000 establishments in Spain]]\n[[Category:Korea friendship associations]]\n[[Category:North Korea\u2013Spain relations]]\n[[Category:Organizations specializing in North Korean issues]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Voluntary association}}\n{{third-party|date=May 2016}}\n{{Infobox organization\n|name           = Korean Friendship Association\n|image          = Korean Friendship Association.png\n|image_border   = \n|size           = \n|alt            = \n|caption        = Korean Friendship Association logo\n|map            = \n|msize          = \n|malt           = \n|mcaption       = \n|abbreviation   = KFA\n|motto          = \n|formation      = {{Start date|2000|11}}\n|extinction     = \n|type           = \n|status         = \n|purpose        = Official government cultural liaison agency for [[North Korea]] \n|headquarters   = \n|location       = Spain\n|region_served  = World\n|membership     = \n|language       = English\n|leader_title   = President\n|leader_name    = [[Alejandro Cao de Ben\u00f3s de Les y P\u00e9rez]]\n|main_organ     = \n|parent_organization = \n|affiliations   = \n|num_staff      = \n|num_volunteers = \n|budget         = \n|website        = {{URL|http://www.korea-dpr.com/kfa.html}}\n|remarks        = Hymn: [[Song of National Defense]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/NorthKoreaDPRK/status/326299450966421504|title=Official KFA Hymn Song of National Defence|publisher=KFA Official Twitter Account|date=April 22, 2013|accessdate=December 12, 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n\nThe '''Korean Friendship Association''' ({{lang-es|Asociaci\u00f3n de Amistad con Corea}}) is a [[Spain|Spanish]]-based friendship association with [[North Korea]]. The KFA was established in November 2000.<ref name=\"James2012\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nknews.org/2012/01/useful-idiots-the-curious-case-of-britains-pro-north-korean-community/|title='Useful Idiots'? The curious case of Britain's pro-North Korean Community|first=\nAlexander|last=James|date=29 January 2012|access-date=27 May 2016|website=NK News}}</ref> It has official representatives in 34 countries, including [[Argentina]], [[Belgium]], [[Brazil]], [[Canada]], [[China]], the [[Czech Republic]], [[Germany]], [[Greece]], [[Israel]] and [[State of Palestine|Palestine]], [[Italy]], [[Mexico]], [[Morocco]], [[Norway]], [[Peru]], [[Russia]], Spain, [[Switzerland]], [[Turkey]], the [[United Kingdom]], and the [[United States]].{{Citation needed lead|date=December 2016}}\n\nIts president, [[Spain|Spanish]] citizen [[Alejandro Cao de Ben\u00f3s de Les y P\u00e9rez]], is the only person paid a salary. Fees collected by the KFA are generally deposited in accounts in his name around Europe.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Capitalist credentials: N. Korea sympathizer group's huge profit on access to country|url = http://www.nknews.org/2015/01/capitalist-credentials-n-korea-sympathizer-groups-huge-profit-on-access-to-country/|website = NK News - North Korea News|access-date = 2016-01-13}}</ref>\n\n==Line==\nCompared with other North Korea friendship associations, the KFA is more radical.<ref name=\"Diplomat2014\">{{cite web|url=http://thediplomat.com/2014/02/the-westerners-who-love-north-korea/|title=The Westerners Who Love North Korea|first=Johan|last=Nylander|date=25 February 2014|access-date=27 May 2016|work=The Diplomat}}</ref>\n\nThe KFA pages provides North Korean related material, including tourism tips and political essays, and it is possible to hear views from a North Korean perspective. The KFA Forum site is hosted and administered in Europe and gives links to Korean language teaching sites.\n\nThe KFA denies violations of [[human rights in North Korea]] and disputes the existence of [[List of concentration and internment camps#North Korea|North Korean concentration camps]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Alejandro Cao de Ben\u00f3s Interview Part 2|work=One Free Korea|author=Enzo Reale|date=February 7, 2010|url= http://freekorea.us/2010/02/07/alejandro-cao-de-benos-interview-%E2%80%93-part-2/|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref>  \n\nThe objectives of the KFA are to promote the well-being of all members and to promote friendship between members of the KFA worldwide.\n\n===Objectives===\nThe stated objectives of the KFA are:<ref>http://www.korea-dpr.com/kfa.html</ref>\n* Show the reality of North Korea to the world. \n* Defend the independence and socialist construction in North Korea. \n* Learn from the culture and history of the Korean People - Work for the peaceful [[Korean reunification|unification]] of the [[Korean peninsula]].\n\nThe KFA organizes travel delegations to North Korea.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1699876,00.html|title=Postcard. North Korea|first=Jeann|last=\nGearey|date=3 January 2008|access-date=27 May 2016|website=Time|url-access=subscription }}</ref> Travel is according to experts a primary motivation of membership in KFA: partakers in trips are offered privileged service.<ref name=\"Harlan2012\"/>\n\n==Structure==\nThe KFA is the largest friendship association with North Korea.<ref name=\"Diplomat2014\"/> It operates in 120 countries. There is an Official Delegate in 34 countries. The KFA is licensed by the [[North Korean government]] and is well-funded and supported. The organization is coordinated well \"to a certain degree\", according to [[NK News]].<ref name=\"James2012\"/>\n\nThe national associations under the KFA do not receive official funding and operate \"as far less than consulates, just slightly more than fan clubs\".<ref name=\"Harlan2012\"/> They do not have many functions to support the government of North Korea: they do not support the regime monetarily and do not gather intelligence.<ref name=\"Harlan2012\">{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/asia_pacific/n-korea-finds-a-purpose-for-small-group-of-friends/2012/02/24/gIQAGHuImR_story.html|title=\nN. Korea finds a purpose for small group of 'friends'|first=Chico|last=Harlan|date=March 2, 2012|access-date=27 May 2016|website=The Washington Post}}</ref>\n\nOfficial Delegates are responsible for the activities in his/her country and secretaries appointed by the delegates. Above the Official Delegates, the \"International Organization Committee\" consisting of the President, the International Counselor and an International Organization Secretary who control and direct the activities of the KFA worldwide.\n*President: Alejandro Cao de Ben\u00f3s de Les y P\u00e9rez\n*International organization secretary: Mana Sapmak\n*International communication secretary: Carlos Luna\n*International Self-Elected Secretariat: Cory Ray Pope Giles-d'Leeuw\n*International commissar: Trever Aritz <ref>[http://korea-dpr.com/organization.html Official homepage]</ref>\n*Some of the most active members are Dr. Dermot Hudson, the Official Delegate in the United Kingdom who has been a part of KFA since its beginning and Trevor Spencer, the Official Delegate in Canada who is an active political writer and commentator.\n*Only one person has 4 countries as Zone delegate, Mr. Ulrich Larsen from Denmark. Ulrich Larsen is the Zone delegate in Scandinavia, meaning that he is in charge of Denmark, Finland, Norway, and Sweden. Larsen is known for making films about North Korea to YouTube for propaganda use. Both Dr. Dermot Hudson and Ulrich Larsen have been awarded medals by the North Korean government. \n\n==Criticism==\n[[NK News]] describes the KFA as \"one of the DPRK's primary tools of soft power within its global propaganda network\".<ref name=\"James2012\"/>\n\nJournalist David Scofield of [[Asia Times|Asia Times Online]] called members of KFA \"[[useful idiot]]s\",<ref name=\"Scofield2005\"/> described the organization as follows:\n\n<blockquote>The group's activities include \"information\" seminars where the enlightened benevolence of Kim's rule is championed, all part of its \"alternative\" view of the North. The ragged wretched displays of poverty and starvation are edited out and the voice of North Koreans not in the direct employ of Kim Jong-il are conspicuously absent. In place of uncomfortable reality, the KFA offers vacation photos of \"their\" North Korea taken during recent, state-supported visits, complete with bowling, golf, amusement parks and Karaoke with young female party members. Members write glowing pieces, oblations celebrating Kim Jong-il's wise rule. No starving people, torture, summary execution, penury or despair in the Korean Friendship Association's North Korea. Just golf, great meals and evenings in the company of Kim Jong-il's beauties.<ref name=\"Scofield2005\">{{cite web|url=http://www.atimes.com/atimes/Korea/GB03Dg02.html|title=\t\nKim Jong-il's 'useful idiots' in the West|first=David|last=Scofield|date=February 3, 2005|accessdate=December 28, 2013}}</ref></blockquote>\n\nA 2015 investigation by NK News found the commercial practices and integrity of the KFA to be in question.<ref>[http://www.nknews.org/2015/01/capitalist-credentials-n-korea-sympathizer-groups-huge-profit-on-access-to-country/ Capitalist credentials: N. Korea sympathizer group's huge profit on access to country]</ref>\n\nAccording to Hazel Smith of [[Cranfield University]], KFA associations have lost much of their original role as part of an international socialist movement. Today, they are reduced to serving domestic purposes of North Korea.<ref name=\"Harlan2012\"/>\n\n===International relations===\n\nThe KFA does not recognize, support or refer to any other Korean Friendship Associations around the world, including those who provide humanitarian aid as a main part of their action plan.  They refuse to create links on their own website to these organisations seeing themselves as \"the one and only Korean Friendship Association\", however, they are willing to participate in seminars and meetings in Pyongyang with these other international organisations.{{Citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|North Korea}}\n\n* [[Politics of North Korea]]\n* [[Propaganda in North Korea]]\n* [[Cultural diplomacy]]\n* [[Public diplomacy]]\n* [[Swedish-Korean Association]]\n* [[British Council]]\n* [[Alliance Fran\u00e7aise]]\n* [[German-American Bund]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website}}\n\n[[Category:Spanish friendship associations]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 2000]]\n[[Category:2000 establishments in Spain]]\n[[Category:Korea friendship associations]]\n[[Category:North Korea\u2013Spain relations]]\n[[Category:Organizations specializing in North Korean issues]]\n", "name_user": "Mertinfegertin", "label": "safe", "comment": "it had to be fixed !", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Korean_Friendship_Association"}
{"title_page": "David Ayres", "text_new": "{{For|the 19th-century American soldier|David Ayers}}\n{{distinguish|David Ayer|David Ayre}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{short description|Canadian ice hockey player}}\n{{Infobox ice hockey player\n| name = David Ayres\n| image = \n| caption = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1977|8|12}}\n| birth_place = [[Whitby, Ontario]], Canada\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in = 0\n| weight_lbs = 201\n| position = Goaltender\n| catches = Left\n| league = \n| team = \n| prospect_league = \n| prospect_team = \n| played_for = [[Carolina Hurricanes]]\n| ntl_team = \n| draft = Undrafted\n| draft_year = \n| draft_team = \n| career_start = 2014\n| career_end = 2015<br>2020\n}}\n'''David Ayres''' (born August 12, 1977) is a Canadian ice hockey player, the first and only emergency backup goaltender to record a win in the history of the [[National Hockey League]] (NHL). He is also the operations manager at the [[Mattamy Athletic Centre]] in [[Toronto]], Ontario.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Venn |first1=David |title=What they're saying about him: Hurricanes' emergency back-up goalie David Ayres becomes a sports sensation overnight |url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2020/02/23/what-theyre-saying-about-him-emergency-back-up-goaltender-david-ayres-becomes-a-sports-sensation-overnight.html |accessdate=February 27, 2020 |work=Toronto Star |date=February 23, 2020}}</ref>\n\nAyres is best known for playing in a [[NHL]] game on February 22, 2020, for the [[Carolina Hurricanes]] as an [[emergency backup goalie|emergency backup goaltender]], beating the [[Toronto Maple Leafs]], 6\u20133, and becoming the first emergency goaltender to record a win in NHL history.<ref>{{cite web |title = David Ayres |url = https://www.eliteprospects.com/player/400710/david-ayres |website = EliteProspects |access-date = February 22, 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1 = Williams |first1 = Thomas |title = Hurricanes' Mrazek replaced by emergency goalie David Ayres after collision |url = https://sports.yahoo.com/hurricanes-mrazek-leaves-game-after-collision-with-maple-leafs-clifford-020107536.html |website = Yahoo! Sports |access-date = February 22, 2020 |date = February 22, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==Early and personal life==\nAyres is a native of [[Whitby, Ontario]], and grew up playing youth [[ice hockey]] and camps in the town. His late father, Bob, and his brother, Chris, were also goaltenders.<ref name=\"ketko\">{{cite news |last1 = Ketko |first1 = Thomas |title = Player of Interest: Who is Hurricanes emergency goalie David Ayres? |url = https://www.sportsnet.ca/hockey/nhl/hurricanes-emergency-goalie-david-ayres/ |access-date = February 22, 2020 |work = Sportsnet.ca |date = February 22, 2020 }}</ref> He became ill and required a [[kidney transplant]] (donated by his mother, Mary) in 2004.<ref name=\"kaplan\"/>\n\nAyres worked as a building operator at Ricoh Coliseum (now [[Coca-Cola Coliseum]]) in [[Toronto]], which is the home arena for the [[Toronto Marlies]].  His job responsibilities occasionally included maintenance and operating an [[ice resurfacer]], which gave him the \"[[Zamboni Company|Zamboni]] driver\" moniker used in news articles about his NHL debut.<ref name=\"WSJ\">{{Cite news |last = Gay |first = Jason |url = https://www.wsj.com/articles/he-went-to-a-hockey-game-expecting-dinner-he-wound-up-getting-the-win-11582554854 |title = He went to a hockey game expecting dinner. He wound up getting the win. |date = February 24, 2020 |work = [[The Wall Street Journal]] |access-date = February 24, 2020 |language = en-US |issn = 0099-9660 }}</ref> The Marlies equipment man found out he was a goalie and coach, so head coach [[Sheldon Keefe]] started using him as a goaltender at practice when an extra man was needed,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hornby |first1=Lance |title='WHAT A MEMORY FOR HIM': David Ayres, 42-year-old Zamboni driver. wins hearts in defeat of Leafs |url=https://torontosun.com/sports/hockey/nhl/toronto-maple-leafs/what-a-night-for-david-ayres |accessdate=February 27, 2020 |work=Toronto Sun |date=February 23, 2020}}</ref> as did the Maple Leafs.<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.sportsnet.ca/hockey/nhl/hurricanes-beat-maple-leafs-help-emergency-backup-dave-ayres/ |title = Hurricanes beat Maple Leafs with help of emergency backup Dave Ayres |last =  |first =  |date = February 22, 2020 |website = Sportsnet |url-status = live |archive-url =  |archive-date =  |access-date = }}</ref>\n\n==Hockey career==\nAyres played eight games with the [[Norwood Vipers]] of the [[Allan Cup Hockey]] League in 2014. As a goaltender, he allowed 58 goals, had a .777 save percentage and an 0\u20138 record.<ref name=\"kaplan\">{{cite news |last1 = Kaplan |first1 = Emily |title = Zamboni driver, 42, stars as emergency goalie for Hurricanes |url = https://www.espn.com/nhl/story/_/id/28761372/zamboni-driver-42-stars-emergency-goalie-hurricanes |access-date = February 22, 2020 |publisher = [[ESPN]] |date = February 22, 2020 }}</ref> Ayres has served as a backup to both the [[Toronto Marlies]] and [[Charlotte Checkers]] in the [[American Hockey League]] (AHL), the primary affiliates of the Toronto Maple Leafs and Carolina Hurricanes, respectively.<ref name=\"ketko\" />\n\n===NHL appearance===\nOn February 22, both of the [[Carolina Hurricanes]]' goaltenders, [[James Reimer (ice hockey)|James Reimer]] and [[Petr Mrazek]], were injured during a game against the Maple Leafs. Ayres entered the game during the second period as the emergency backup goaltender, after signing a one-game contract with the NHL.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sportingnews.com/ca/nhl/news/who-is-david-ayres-everything-you-need-to-know-about-the-ebug-that-helped-beat-the-maple-leafs/5u4ba5ihk1391x2a6tigh9eqg |title = Who is David Ayres? Everything you need to know about the EBUG that helped beat the Maple Leafs |last = Jarden |first = Sam |date = February 22, 2020 |website = Sporting News |url-status = live |archive-url =  |archive-date =  |access-date = }}</ref> Donning [[Kasimir Kaskisuo]]'s old [[Toronto Marlies]] helmet and pads,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nhl/2020/02/23/david-ayres-hurricanes-emergency-goalie/4849645002/|title=Meet David Ayres, the Hurricanes' emergency goalie. He is a Zamboni driver who will practice with Maple Leafs|first=Jimmy|last=Hascup|website=USA Today}}</ref> and wearing a Maple Leafs t-shirt under his equipment,<ref>{{Cite tweet |url=https://twitter.com/lukefoxjukebox/status/1231414649934970880 |number = 1231414649934970880 |title=Dave Ayres was wearing a Leafs T-shirt under his Hurricanes uniform.|last=Fox|first=Luke|date=February 22, 2020|user = lukefoxjukebox |access-date=February 25, 2020  }}</ref> he entered the game at 8:41 left in the 2nd period with a 3-1 lead.<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.nhl.com/gamecenter/car-vs-tor/2020/02/22/2019020951 |title = Carolina Hurricanes - Toronto Maple Leafs - February 22nd, 2020 |publisher = [[National Hockey League]] }}</ref> He allowed goals on the first two shots that he faced before stopping the next eight shots on goal, along with recording one shot on goal, to help seal a 6\u20133 win for Carolina.<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.cbc.ca/sports/hockey/nhl/toronto-maple-leafs-carolina-hurricanes-feb-22-recap-1.5472758 |title = Emergency backup goalie David Ayres steals show in Canes' win over Leafs |last = Clipperton |first = Joshua |date = February 22, 2020 |website = CBC Sports |url-status = live |archive-url =  |archive-date =  |access-date = }}</ref> He became the first emergency backup to enter a game in the NHL since [[Scott Foster (ice hockey)|Scott Foster]] in 2018.<ref name=\"kaplan\" /> Ayres also became the oldest goaltender (at 42 years, 194 days) to win his NHL regular-season debut, and for this, the [[Hockey Hall of Fame]] was given his game-used goalie stick.<ref>{{cite tweet |user = PR_NHL |author = NHL Public Relations |number = 1231414103241035776 |title = David Ayres (42 years, 194 days) became the oldest goaltender in NHL history to win his regular-season debut. |date = February 22, 2020 |access-date = February 23, 2020 |link = no }}</ref><ref name=\"TheStar20200223\">{{Cite web |url = https://www.thestar.com/sports/hockey/2020/02/23/ayres-whirlwind-continues-as-hurricanes-announce-he-will-be-in-the-building-for-next-home-game.html |title = A day in his honour, stick in the Hall of Fame, booked on The Today Show. It's good to be David Ayres |date = February 23, 2020 |website = The Star |language = en |access-date = February 25, 2020 }}</ref> The record had been held by [[Hughie Lehman|Hugh Lehman]] since 1927 at 41 years 21 days.\n\nAyres was named first star of the game and kept his game-worn jersey and game puck.<ref name=\":0\" /> Had he signed a Professional Try-Out Agreement he would have been paid $500 for the game,<ref name=\"fernandez20200224\">{{Cite web |url = https://www.cbssports.com/nhl/news/emergency-goalie-david-ayres-helps-hurricanes-defeat-maple-leafs-in-wild-nhl-debut/ |title = Emergency goalie David Ayres helps Hurricanes defeat Maple Leafs in wild NHL debut |last = Fernandez |first = Gabriel |date = February 24, 2020 |website = CBS Sports |language = en |access-date = February 24, 2020 }}</ref> but Ayres said after the game that under the terms of his contract he was not paid.<ref name=WSJ/> Reimer also gave him an autographed goalie stick, and [[Rod Brind'Amour]], Carolina's coach, gave Ayres an autographed bottle of wine.<ref>{{cite news |title = Ayres on unlikely NHL debut : 'Absolutely I was nervous!' |url = https://www.tsn.ca/nhl/video/ayres-on-unlikely-nhl-debut-absolutely-i-was-nervous~1906878 |publisher = [[The Sports Network]] |date = February 22, 2020 }}</ref> His debut occurred on the 40th anniversary of the [[Miracle on Ice]].<ref>{{cite news |first = Barry |last = Werner |date = February 22, 2020 |title = Miracle on Ice in Toronto as Hurricanes win with 42-year-old Zamboni driver as emergency goaltender |url = https://touchdownwire.usatoday.com/2020/02/22/miracle-on-ice-in-toronto-as-hurricanes-win-with-42-year-old-zamboni-driver-emergency-goaltender/ |department = Touchdown Wire |work = USA Today |access-date = February 23, 2020 }}</ref>\n\nFollowing the game, the Carolina Hurricanes announced that they would be selling t-shirts with Ayres' name and jersey number 90, with royalties going to Ayres and a portion of the proceeds being donated to a kidney foundation of Ayres' choice.<ref>{{cite tweet |author = Carolina Hurricanes |user = Canes |number = 1231439385905827840 |title = Dave will be getting royalties, but we are also working with him to identify a kidney foundation that will receive a portion of the proceeds |date = February 22, 2020 |access-date = February 23, 2020 |link = no }}</ref>\n\nAyres was invited to sound the siren at the start of the Carolina Hurricanes home game, on February 25. While in North Carolina, Governor [[Roy Cooper]] declared Ayres, a Canadian citizen, an honorary citizen of the state of North Carolina,<ref>{{Cite press release |url = https://governor.nc.gov/news/governor-roy-cooper-proclaims-emergency-goalie-david-ayres-honorary-north-carolinian |title = Governor Roy Cooper Proclaims Emergency Goalie David Ayres as an Honorary North Carolinian |last = Porter |first = Ford |date = February 25, 2020 |publisher = North Carolina Office of the Governor |url-status = live |archive-url = |archive-date = |access-date = February 26, 2020 }}</ref> and [[Raleigh, North Carolina|Raleigh]] honoured him by naming February 25, 2020 \"David Ayres Day\" in the City of Raleigh.<ref name=\"Tweet-1231658150186471424\">{{cite tweet |first = Mary-Ann |last = Baldwin  |user = maryannbaldwin |url = https://mobile.twitter.com/maryannbaldwin/status/1231658150186471424 |number = 1231658150186471424 |author= @maryannbaldwin |title= The City will be honoring him with a formal proclamation, naming Tuesday 'DAVID AYRES DAY' in Raleigh. I'm sorry I can\u2019t be there to present it but I'm thrilled that @Canes fans will have the opportunity to share this joy. #livingthedream |date= February 23, 2020 |access-date = February 26, 2020 |link = no }}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Regular season===\n{| border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"text-align:center; width:75%\"\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! align=\"center\" colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" |  \n! align=\"center\" rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" |  \n! colspan=\"10\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\" align=\"center\" | [[Regular season]]\n! align=\"center\" rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" |  \n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! [[Season (sports)|Season]]\n! Team\n! League\n! {{tooltip|GP|Games played}}\n! {{tooltip|W|Wins}}\n! {{tooltip|L|Losses}}\n! {{tooltip|OTL|Overtime losses}}\n! {{tooltip|TOI|Time on ice (minutes:seconds)}}\n! {{tooltip|SA|Shots against}}\n! {{tooltip|GA|Goals against}}\n! {{tooltip|SO|Shutouts}}\n! {{tooltip|GAA|Goals against average}}\n! {{tooltip|SV%|Save percentage}}\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 2014\u201315\n| [[Norwood Vipers]]\n| [[Allan Cup Hockey|ACH]]\n| 8\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| 8.88\n| .777\n|- bgcolor=\"#f0f0f0\" ALIGN=\"center\"\n| [[2019\u201320 NHL season|2019\u201320]]\n| [[Carolina Hurricanes]]\n| [[National Hockey League|NHL]]\n| 1\n| 1\n| 0\n| 0\n| 28:41\n| 10\n| 2\n| 0\n| 4.18\n| .800\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\" | NHL totals\n! 1\n! 1\n! 0\n! 0\n! 28:41\n! 10\n! 2\n! 0\n! 4.18\n! .800\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Jorge Alves (ice hockey)|Jorge Alves]] \u2013 Carolina Hurricanes equipment manager who played as a backup goalie for his team on December 31, 2016\n* [[Lester Patrick#New York Rangers|Lester Patrick]] \u2013 former New York Rangers coach who, at age 44, played in the 1928 Stanley Cup Finals for the team as an emergency goalie\n*[[List of players who played only one game in the NHL]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Ice Hockey Stats|nhl=8479188|elite=400710|espn=4641047|euro=|hr=a/ayresda01|hockeydb=232235|legendsm=|legends=|legendstype=|tsn=}}\n* [https://pbs.twimg.com/media/ERocgzCUUAA4EI7.jpg Honorary Citizenship Proclamation for David Ayres] by Governor Roy Cooper\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ayres, David}}\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Canadian ice hockey goaltenders]]\n[[Category:Carolina Hurricanes players]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey people from Ontario]]\n[[Category:Kidney transplant recipients]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Whitby, Ontario]]\n[[Category:Maple Leaf Sports & Entertainment]]\n[[Category:Undrafted National Hockey League players]]\n", "text_old": "{{For|the 19th-century American soldier|David Ayers}}\n{{distinguish|David Ayer|David Ayre}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{short description|Canadian ice hockey player}}\n{{Infobox ice hockey player\n| name = David Ayres\n| image = \n| caption = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1977|8|12}}\n| birth_place = [[Whitby, Ontario]], Canada\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in = 0\n| weight_lbs = 201\n| position = Goaltender\n| catches = Left\n| league = \n| team = \n| prospect_league = \n| prospect_team = \n| played_for = [[Carolina Hurricanes]]\n| ntl_team = \n| draft = Undrafted\n| draft_year = \n| draft_team = \n| career_start = 2014\n| career_end = 2015<br>2020\n}}\n'''David Ayres''' (born August 12, 1977) is a Canadian ice hockey player, the first and only emergency backup goaltender to record a win in the history of the [[National Hockey League]] (NHL). He is also the operations manager at the [[Mattamy Athletic Centre]] in [[Toronto]], Ontario.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Venn |first1=David |title=What they're saying about him: Hurricanes' emergency back-up goalie David Ayres becomes a sports sensation overnight |url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2020/02/23/what-theyre-saying-about-him-emergency-back-up-goaltender-david-ayres-becomes-a-sports-sensation-overnight.html |accessdate=February 27, 2020 |work=Toronto Star |date=February 23, 2020}}</ref>\n\nAyres is best known for playing in a [[NHL]] game on February 22, 2020, for the [[Carolina Hurricanes]] as an [[emergency backup goalie|emergency backup goaltender]], beating the [[Toronto Maple Leafs]], 6\u20133, and becoming the first emergency goaltender to record a win in NHL history.<ref>{{cite web |title = David Ayres |url = https://www.eliteprospects.com/player/400710/david-ayres |website = EliteProspects |access-date = February 22, 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1 = Williams |first1 = Thomas |title = Hurricanes' Mrazek replaced by emergency goalie David Ayres after collision |url = https://sports.yahoo.com/hurricanes-mrazek-leaves-game-after-collision-with-maple-leafs-clifford-020107536.html |website = Yahoo! Sports |access-date = February 22, 2020 |date = February 22, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==Early and personal life==\nAyres is a native of [[Whitby, Ontario]], and grew up playing youth [[ice hockey]] and camps in the town. His late father, Bob, and his brother, Chris, were also goaltenders.<ref name=\"ketko\">{{cite news |last1 = Ketko |first1 = Thomas |title = Player of Interest: Who is Hurricanes emergency goalie David Ayres? |url = https://www.sportsnet.ca/hockey/nhl/hurricanes-emergency-goalie-david-ayres/ |access-date = February 22, 2020 |work = Sportsnet.ca |date = February 22, 2020 }}</ref> He became ill and required a [[kidney transplant]] (donated by his mother, Mary) in 2004.<ref name=\"kaplan\"/>\n\nAyres worked as a building operator at Ricoh Coliseum (now [[Coca-Cola Coliseum]]) in [[Toronto]], which is the home arena for the [[Toronto Marlies]].  His job responsibilities occasionally included maintenance and operating an [[ice resurfacer]], which gave him the \"[[Zamboni Company|Zamboni]] driver\" moniker used in news articles about his NHL [[debut (disambiguation)|debut]].<ref name=\"WSJ\">{{Cite news |last = Gay |first = Jason |url = https://www.wsj.com/articles/he-went-to-a-hockey-game-expecting-dinner-he-wound-up-getting-the-win-11582554854 |title = He went to a hockey game expecting dinner. He wound up getting the win. |date = February 24, 2020 |work = [[The Wall Street Journal]] |access-date = February 24, 2020 |language = en-US |issn = 0099-9660 }}</ref> The Marlies equipment man found out he was a goalie and coach, so head coach [[Sheldon Keefe]] started using him as a goaltender at practice when an extra man was needed,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hornby |first1=Lance |title='WHAT A MEMORY FOR HIM': David Ayres, 42-year-old Zamboni driver. wins hearts in defeat of Leafs |url=https://torontosun.com/sports/hockey/nhl/toronto-maple-leafs/what-a-night-for-david-ayres |accessdate=February 27, 2020 |work=Toronto Sun |date=February 23, 2020}}</ref> as did the Maple Leafs.<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.sportsnet.ca/hockey/nhl/hurricanes-beat-maple-leafs-help-emergency-backup-dave-ayres/ |title = Hurricanes beat Maple Leafs with help of emergency backup Dave Ayres |last =  |first =  |date = February 22, 2020 |website = Sportsnet |url-status = live |archive-url =  |archive-date =  |access-date = }}</ref>\n\n==Hockey career==\nAyres played eight games with the [[Norwood Vipers]] of the [[Allan Cup Hockey]] League in 2014. As a goaltender, he allowed 58 goals, had a .777 save percentage and an 0\u20138 record.<ref name=\"kaplan\">{{cite news |last1 = Kaplan |first1 = Emily |title = Zamboni driver, 42, stars as emergency goalie for Hurricanes |url = https://www.espn.com/nhl/story/_/id/28761372/zamboni-driver-42-stars-emergency-goalie-hurricanes |access-date = February 22, 2020 |publisher = [[ESPN]] |date = February 22, 2020 }}</ref> Ayres has served as a backup to both the [[Toronto Marlies]] and [[Charlotte Checkers]] in the [[American Hockey League]] (AHL), the primary affiliates of the Toronto Maple Leafs and Carolina Hurricanes, respectively.<ref name=\"ketko\" />\n\n===NHL appearance===\nOn February 22, both of the [[Carolina Hurricanes]]' goaltenders, [[James Reimer (ice hockey)|James Reimer]] and [[Petr Mrazek]], were injured during a game against the Maple Leafs. Ayres entered the game during the second period as the emergency backup goaltender, after signing a one-game contract with the NHL.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sportingnews.com/ca/nhl/news/who-is-david-ayres-everything-you-need-to-know-about-the-ebug-that-helped-beat-the-maple-leafs/5u4ba5ihk1391x2a6tigh9eqg |title = Who is David Ayres? Everything you need to know about the EBUG that helped beat the Maple Leafs |last = Jarden |first = Sam |date = February 22, 2020 |website = Sporting News |url-status = live |archive-url =  |archive-date =  |access-date = }}</ref> Donning [[Kasimir Kaskisuo]]'s old [[Toronto Marlies]] helmet and pads,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nhl/2020/02/23/david-ayres-hurricanes-emergency-goalie/4849645002/|title=Meet David Ayres, the Hurricanes' emergency goalie. He is a Zamboni driver who will practice with Maple Leafs|first=Jimmy|last=Hascup|website=USA Today}}</ref> and wearing a Maple Leafs t-shirt under his equipment,<ref>{{Cite tweet |url=https://twitter.com/lukefoxjukebox/status/1231414649934970880 |number = 1231414649934970880 |title=Dave Ayres was wearing a Leafs T-shirt under his Hurricanes uniform.|last=Fox|first=Luke|date=February 22, 2020|user = lukefoxjukebox |access-date=February 25, 2020  }}</ref> he entered the game at 8:41 left in the 2nd period with a 3-1 lead.<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.nhl.com/gamecenter/car-vs-tor/2020/02/22/2019020951 |title = Carolina Hurricanes - Toronto Maple Leafs - February 22nd, 2020 |publisher = [[National Hockey League]] }}</ref> He allowed goals on the first two shots that he faced before stopping the next eight shots on goal, along with recording one shot on goal, to help seal a 6\u20133 win for Carolina.<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.cbc.ca/sports/hockey/nhl/toronto-maple-leafs-carolina-hurricanes-feb-22-recap-1.5472758 |title = Emergency backup goalie David Ayres steals show in Canes' win over Leafs |last = Clipperton |first = Joshua |date = February 22, 2020 |website = CBC Sports |url-status = live |archive-url =  |archive-date =  |access-date = }}</ref> He became the first emergency backup to enter a game in the NHL since [[Scott Foster (ice hockey)|Scott Foster]] in 2018.<ref name=\"kaplan\" /> Ayres also became the oldest goaltender (at 42 years, 194 days) to win his NHL regular-season debut, and for this, the [[Hockey Hall of Fame]] was given his game-used goalie stick.<ref>{{cite tweet |user = PR_NHL |author = NHL Public Relations |number = 1231414103241035776 |title = David Ayres (42 years, 194 days) became the oldest goaltender in NHL history to win his regular-season debut. |date = February 22, 2020 |access-date = February 23, 2020 |link = no }}</ref><ref name=\"TheStar20200223\">{{Cite web |url = https://www.thestar.com/sports/hockey/2020/02/23/ayres-whirlwind-continues-as-hurricanes-announce-he-will-be-in-the-building-for-next-home-game.html |title = A day in his honour, stick in the Hall of Fame, booked on The Today Show. It's good to be David Ayres |date = February 23, 2020 |website = The Star |language = en |access-date = February 25, 2020 }}</ref> The record had been held by [[Hughie Lehman|Hugh Lehman]] since 1927 at 41 years 21 days.\n\nAyres was named first star of the game and kept his game-worn jersey and game puck.<ref name=\":0\" /> Had he signed a Professional Try-Out Agreement he would have been paid $500 for the game,<ref name=\"fernandez20200224\">{{Cite web |url = https://www.cbssports.com/nhl/news/emergency-goalie-david-ayres-helps-hurricanes-defeat-maple-leafs-in-wild-nhl-debut/ |title = Emergency goalie David Ayres helps Hurricanes defeat Maple Leafs in wild NHL debut |last = Fernandez |first = Gabriel |date = February 24, 2020 |website = CBS Sports |language = en |access-date = February 24, 2020 }}</ref> but Ayres said after the game that under the terms of his contract he was not paid.<ref name=WSJ/> Reimer also gave him an autographed goalie stick, and [[Rod Brind'Amour]], Carolina's coach, gave Ayres an autographed bottle of wine.<ref>{{cite news |title = Ayres on unlikely NHL debut : 'Absolutely I was nervous!' |url = https://www.tsn.ca/nhl/video/ayres-on-unlikely-nhl-debut-absolutely-i-was-nervous~1906878 |publisher = [[The Sports Network]] |date = February 22, 2020 }}</ref> His debut occurred on the 40th anniversary of the [[Miracle on Ice]].<ref>{{cite news |first = Barry |last = Werner |date = February 22, 2020 |title = Miracle on Ice in Toronto as Hurricanes win with 42-year-old Zamboni driver as emergency goaltender |url = https://touchdownwire.usatoday.com/2020/02/22/miracle-on-ice-in-toronto-as-hurricanes-win-with-42-year-old-zamboni-driver-emergency-goaltender/ |department = Touchdown Wire |work = USA Today |access-date = February 23, 2020 }}</ref>\n\nFollowing the game, the Carolina Hurricanes announced that they would be selling t-shirts with Ayres' name and jersey number 90, with royalties going to Ayres and a portion of the proceeds being donated to a kidney foundation of Ayres' choice.<ref>{{cite tweet |author = Carolina Hurricanes |user = Canes |number = 1231439385905827840 |title = Dave will be getting royalties, but we are also working with him to identify a kidney foundation that will receive a portion of the proceeds |date = February 22, 2020 |access-date = February 23, 2020 |link = no }}</ref>\n\nAyres was invited to sound the siren at the start of the Carolina Hurricanes home game, on February 25. While in North Carolina, Governor [[Roy Cooper]] declared Ayres, a Canadian citizen, an honorary citizen of the state of North Carolina,<ref>{{Cite press release |url = https://governor.nc.gov/news/governor-roy-cooper-proclaims-emergency-goalie-david-ayres-honorary-north-carolinian |title = Governor Roy Cooper Proclaims Emergency Goalie David Ayres as an Honorary North Carolinian |last = Porter |first = Ford |date = February 25, 2020 |publisher = North Carolina Office of the Governor |url-status = live |archive-url = |archive-date = |access-date = February 26, 2020 }}</ref> and [[Raleigh, North Carolina|Raleigh]] honoured him by naming February 25, 2020 \"David Ayres Day\" in the City of Raleigh.<ref name=\"Tweet-1231658150186471424\">{{cite tweet |first = Mary-Ann |last = Baldwin  |user = maryannbaldwin |url = https://mobile.twitter.com/maryannbaldwin/status/1231658150186471424 |number = 1231658150186471424 |author= @maryannbaldwin |title= The City will be honoring him with a formal proclamation, naming Tuesday 'DAVID AYRES DAY' in Raleigh. I'm sorry I can\u2019t be there to present it but I'm thrilled that @Canes fans will have the opportunity to share this joy. #livingthedream |date= February 23, 2020 |access-date = February 26, 2020 |link = no }}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Regular season===\n{| border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"text-align:center; width:75%\"\n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! align=\"center\" colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" |  \n! align=\"center\" rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" |  \n! colspan=\"10\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\" align=\"center\" | [[Regular season]]\n! align=\"center\" rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" |  \n|- ALIGN=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\"\n! [[Season (sports)|Season]]\n! Team\n! League\n! {{tooltip|GP|Games played}}\n! {{tooltip|W|Wins}}\n! {{tooltip|L|Losses}}\n! {{tooltip|OTL|Overtime losses}}\n! {{tooltip|TOI|Time on ice (minutes:seconds)}}\n! {{tooltip|SA|Shots against}}\n! {{tooltip|GA|Goals against}}\n! {{tooltip|SO|Shutouts}}\n! {{tooltip|GAA|Goals against average}}\n! {{tooltip|SV%|Save percentage}}\n|- ALIGN=\"center\"\n| 2014\u201315\n| [[Norwood Vipers]]\n| [[Allan Cup Hockey|ACH]]\n| 8\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u