{"title_page": "H\u0103ghig", "text_new": "{{for|the river in Covasna County|H\u0103ghig (river)}}\n{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = commune\n|county                 = Covasna\n|population_total       = auto\n|map_caption            = Location in Covasna County\n|subdivisions           = \n|official_name=H\u0103ghig\n|other_name=H\u00eddv\u00e9g\n|image_shield=\n|image_map=Haghig jud Covasna.png\n|leader_name=Alexandru Cucu<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.2016bec.ro/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/SIAL2016_P_Lista_Moc-2.xlsx |title=Results of the 2016 local elections |publisher=Central Electoral Bureau |accessdate=2020-04-06 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|leader_party=PSD\n|area_total_km2=\n|coordinates = {{coord|45|50|N|25|35|E|region:RO|display=inline,title}}\n|website=\n}}\n\n'''H\u0103ghig''' ({{lang-hu|H\u00eddv\u00e9g}}, <small>Hungarian pronunciation</small>: {{convertIPA-hu|\u2019|h|\u00ed|d|v|\u00e9|g}}) is a commune in [[Covasna County]], [[Romania]] composed of two villages:\n*'''H\u0103ghig'''\n*Iar\u0103\u0219 / Ny\u00e1raspatak\n\n==Demographics==\n\nThe commune has an ethnically mixed population. According to the 2011 [[census]], it has a population of 2,258 of which 41.18% or 930 are [[Romanian people|Romanians]], 30.55% or 690 are [[Romani people|Roma]] and 28.12% or 635 are [[Sz\u00e9kely]] [[Hungarian people|Hungarians]]. \n\n{{Covasna County}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Haghig}}\n[[Category:Communes in Covasna County]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the river in Covasna County|H\u0103ghig (river)}}\n{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = commune\n|county                 = Covasna\n|population_total       = auto\n|map_caption            = Location in Covasna County\n|subdivisions           = \n|official_name=H\u0103ghig\n|other_name=H\u00eddv\u00e9g\n|image_shield=\n|image_map=Haghig jud Covasna.png\n|leader_name=Alexandru Cucu\n|leader_party=USL\n|area_total_km2=\n|coordinates = {{coord|45|50|N|25|35|E|region:RO|display=inline,title}}\n|website=\n}}\n\n'''H\u0103ghig''' ({{lang-hu|H\u00eddv\u00e9g}}, <small>Hungarian pronunciation</small>: {{convertIPA-hu|\u2019|h|\u00ed|d|v|\u00e9|g}}) is a commune in [[Covasna County]], [[Romania]] composed of two villages:\n*'''H\u0103ghig'''\n*Iar\u0103\u0219 / Ny\u00e1raspatak\n\n==Demographics==\n\nThe commune has an ethnically mixed population. According to the 2011 [[census]], it has a population of 2,258 of which 41.18% or 930 are [[Romanian people|Romanians]], 30.55% or 690 are [[Romani people|Roma]] and 28.12% or 635 are [[Sz\u00e9kely]] [[Hungarian people|Hungarians]]. \n\n{{Covasna County}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Haghig}}\n[[Category:Communes in Covasna County]]\n", "name_user": "Markussep", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/H%C4%83ghig"}
